abstract={Thanks to their dominant role in fostering socioeconomic prosperity,
exporting small- and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) are perceived to be
a major societal asset. Coming out of the great financial crisis,
initiatives to nurture their (export) competitiveness have been high on
the political agenda. In this vein, a growing literature explores the
pertinence of firm-specific factors for explaining differences in SMEs'
